index.title = Ask your employer for statutory sick pay
index.heading = Ask your employer for statutory sick pay
index.p1 = You may use this form to claim statutory sick pay (SSP) from your employer if you have been sick for 4 or more days in a row and are eligible.
index.beforeYouStart.heading = Before you start
index.beforeYouStart.p1 = You should check with your employer how to notify them of sickness to make sure you follow anything agreed in your employment contract. This may mean you receive more sick pay from your employer, in addition to the statutory sick pay rate.
index.beforeYouStart.p2 = To claim SSP you must also give your employer a fit note if you’re off work for more than 7 days in a row (including non-working days).
index.beforeYouStart.p3 = Once you have completed the form you will need to download it and send it to your employer. If you are sending it in the post you will need a printer.
index.furtherInformation.heading = Further information
index.furtherInformation.p1.1 = You can find out how much you can receive, whether you are eligible and how to claim on the
index.furtherInformation.p1.a = Statutory Sick Pay guidance page
index.furtherInformation.p1.2 = .


